            },
            "answer_text": "On the economic level, the difference between China and Japan lies in the size of the market. The main problem is aging. China's per capita level lags far behind Japan's, and it seems that China's economic situation is not better. However, we should be clear that political economy as a science is not comprehensive only in terms of economy, but also in terms of politics when discussing economy. For China and Japan,It is a zero-sum game to rely solely on current resources to develop in the framework of the existing world order. No one will have a clear momentum for growth. the strong impetus for future development comes from two possibilities. The first is the huge dividend of breaking the current world order , We believe that the world is equal and it is unacceptable that hard-working people staying at the bottom of the pyramid. The second is the huge dividend brought about by the fourth industrial revolution. From this point of view, China and Japan are essentially different. I don't want to analyze them too much. Let's call it a day. ",
